      "writtenOn": "2020-03-19T19:29:37Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think we aren\u0027t relying on data having the same alignment as base_address.\n\ndata is the buffer in the Crashpad handler process containing the stack data read from the target process (e.g. WebView).\n\nbase_address is the address in the target process\u0027 address space from which |data| was read. The alignment of base_address tells us the alignment of |data|\u0027s contents in WebView\u0027s address space, but the alignment of |data| in Crashpad\u0027s address space shouldn\u0027t be relevant.\n\nI do not expect that base_address is always word aligned since it is derived from (and probably often will be equal to) the stack pointer.",
